# **The Imperial Eye Looks Away**

Throughout the past year on BMC, the Imperials have been the most dominant nation on BMC, but more recently, their steam finally seems to be running out.

**Personal Account**

In January of 2026, the BMC ruler of the Imperials, AlmostMee, became the Emperor of all the Imperials across all their servers, leaving Emir to be the Centurion of BMC.
[-Ascension of Almost-](https://discord.com/channels/614275329879572501/616523219813400577/1466918004196376646)

Following this came a period of lack of meaningful or decisive action from the Imperials on BMC. On the 11th of March, Almost pinged everyone on the BMC Imperials server asking for people's help on Stoneworks.

> "I need major help on Stoneworks with a variety of things from Grinders to Builders to Everything, please dm me if you'd like to help, your contributions would count towards promotions here and you will be paid on BMC.
> Those that want to be builders, please also dm me your best builds."

*— Imperials of BendersMC Announcements, 3/11/26*

I applied to do this, as I had always thought that if I were to get into Stoneworks then I'd want to be given some land to build a city. Turns out that was exactly what they wanted — Almost wanted to develop the Imperial lands on Stoneworks and offered me several places to build on. I considered all the land, as well as whether I even wanted to do this for the Imperials. This would mean I'd have to *join the Imperials*, and so I thought maybe I could betray them later on — but why would I join them just to betray them? That would make me an *Imperial* and a *traitor*, the 2 things I hate. I ended up denying their offer.

**Imperial Decline**

Over the whole month of March, the Imperials have had very few announcements. While their main Discord has had several, hardly any of them mention their BMC branch. They have also ramped up their efforts on their other servers such as Donut SMP and Stoneworks. The combination of the resignation of Centurion Emir, the new ascension of Zyn, and the lack of activity from the Imperial BMC branch all point to a drop-off of Imperial focus on BMC. The eye of Sauron has shifted its gaze from BMC.

This is immediately felt. The Elemental Empire has been winning more battles for months, and new members are going to nations other than the Imperials. The Imperials are weakened on BMC — they have an unproven leader, and the other nations of the server stand ready to capitalize on their weakness.

